#OpenComment
In the British Museum,
#Rosetta stone came from Egypt;
the Dunhuang wall paint came from China; 
and the Elgin Marbles came from Greece.
The relics are testimony to both history as well as the pillage of the colonialists.
(Opinion writer Zhang Zhouxiang)
